rComments: This professor is exemplary + has high expectations for her students. We had a in depth reading response of 3 separate and long readings due at the beginning of class each week, each lead the seminar for a class, a presentation of our final papers and final paper. With the reading response she only marked 2/10 we did and they were chosen randomly.

She makes you work for it- you HAVE to go to classes and do every reading beforehand BUT it is SO worth it. I learn more from her in 1 week than an entire semester with some of my other profs. She gives clear criteria&great feedback to make you a better writer and presenter. If you're serious about academia, she is a blessing. So kind and engaging.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Professor Charania's lectures are engaging and interesting. She does not post slides but ensures that the content that is important for evaluations stands out. Be ready to read as her assignments and exams are reading-based. All-in-all an excellent prof who cares about her courses and students - hence this being my fourth class with her!

I've had Dr. Charania for 2 classes now, and would avoid if possible. Extremely, extremely hard grader. That being said she is always available for outside help, and will always says to visit office hours. I have been through a lot of FEM classes but have to say both of the mandatory methodology classes were the worst. Great person, hard teacher.

I was not looking forward to my mandatory methodologies class-after taking her class & learning from her I am so interested in FEM methods& research that I might make it my career. She picks the BEST readings and makes lectures very interesting- but you need to know the readings like the back of your hand & be able to elaborate on the significance

She is so talented at structuring courses & picking a variety of readings. You will learn SO much from her- smartest& most caring woman. Do the readings, attend class & take detailed notes. Engage, be able to explain readings & key concepts as well as critically engage with them. I am a 10000% better reader & writer after her class thanks to her

3rd class with Gulzar & still think she's the best prof. MUST DO READINGS& memorize the main arguments, how they're made, & critically analyze their implications for FEM theory. She pulls out main ideas from readings and sets you up for success if you read & show up to class. Classes very engaging, innovative and critically engaged 100% recommend

Gulzar is one of the most amazing profs you could ever have. She cares about her students immensely and her only goal is to see them succeed. She expects you to do the work, but her readings and lectures are engaging and I always looked forward to them. She expects in-depth knowledge on exams, but it always available to help and provide insight.

A ton of readings that are lengthy, complex yet enjoyable to read. She goes over key "need to knows" about the readings in class. Although she does give out the exam questions, she makes you work for your grades. Shes very good at explaining dense material in class and makes some jokes while shes at it. Attendance matters in her class!

Like everyone else said, keeping up with the readings and knowing all the concepts in them is essential, but she goes through all of the concepts in class so you can do the readings before hand and then go back through after class and summarize the concepts. You need to attend class but she gives participation credit! Amazing prof, TAKE HER!

Yes, you will have to work hard in her class but why pay through the roof to slack off? She bases her exams and assignments directly off of what she and her guest lecturers teach in class (classes are always based on the readings) so if you attend and thoroughly know the readings you can definitely get an A. Be prepared to engage
Gulzar is a nice prof, though she does give the questions for the exam at first, the TAs mark very hard in this class.

Honestly one of the best professors at the university. She has a take no bs attitude yet is still reasonable and caring. Really engages the students. Do the majority of the readings and you'll be fine. She also gives the questions to midterms/finals prior

Gulzar is a gem! She is highly knowledgeable, so her lectures are amazing. She also places a focus on learning from students and fostering group/class discussions. She cares immensely about her students and their success. Course expectations are clear. Teaching is a little unconventional and exam is hard, but she is there to help!

This is not an easy course and the testing is very difficult. You have to memorize quotes from the readings and put them in the exams. She will also give you questions ahead of time except one that you have to put in 2 readings for. You cannot prepare it so it makes it extremely difficult.

Thought this would be a fun elective... Her lectures are somewhat interesting but more in terms of getting you to think rather than giving any actual information. She asks you questions to ponder on but doesn't actually give any answers. Very little guidance as to what she's looking for on midterms/essays, doesn't post slides. Hard grader

Good lecturer, shes quite interesting and explains rather well. Although she wont post any PowerPoints, so be ready to take LOTS of notes. The exam questions are given ahead of time but this means that she grades extremely hard and is very picky about what absolutely needs to be found in your answers.
She lectures pretty much directly from the readings, so going to her class isn't really necessary. She marks fairly on her papers, but her midterms and exams are very hard and require a lot of prep.

rComments: Gulzar is one of the best professors you will ever have! If you ever have a chance to have a class with her, DO IT! She is so passionate and knowledgeable, and will make you fall in love with the content. Her readings are reasonable and interesting. You have to go to class to do well but you want to go to class because her lectures are amazing!

This class was one of the most engaging and interesting classes I have taken at the University, and I truly believe it is because of Professor Charania. I came out  of this class having learned so much.  You need to attend class because lectures aren't posted online. Readings are a must as they are required on the midterm, assignment, and exam.

She is super nice and engaging. She gives you the exam question ahead of time, however, get ready to write a lot on the exams... The exams would literally take me 4 booklets.   The class is easy though!

Great lectures and really lets students participate and everyone has a voice. Nevertheless, midterms and assignments are crazy. You have to do all the readings and do them thoroughly because you have to cite them during exams. I learnt a tons and really enjoyed what she brought to class and all of the guest speakers too. Would recommend.

She really combines lectures and the readings together and loves to reference the readings in her classes. If you do the readings and go to class, super easy A. The content was difficult to understand, but she always tried to clear it up as quickly as possible. Great prof and I would love to have her again.

I have no words to describe her. SHE IS AMAZING.  You will adore her. She is really kind, and I loved how she said "yes?" with a big smile after one raised the hand.  The only thing I did not like, was the bad job that the TA's made. They were just tough and gave NO feedback, even personally. That's the only thing I did not like...

Prof. Charania was a real gem to have as a prof. Her lectures were quite engaging, she brought in guest speakers, and often had the class challenge the way we saw the world. She cared for your grade, but it was your responsibility to work for it. Always available outside of class for extra help. She was also very respectful of other views. 10/10

One of my favourite lecturers and even at 8:30 AM I looked forward to her class. That being said, she exclusively asks questions on exams about quotes and points said in class and only in class specifically (out of like 15 marks) so if you miss 1 or 2 classes you're screwed. A LOT of reading and long exams for an intro course. Tough grader as well

The teacher was great. she had great guest lecturers and videos shown in class. The only thing I found ridiculous was having to memorize specific dates of lectures and reading and then cite those specific dates on the midterm and exam. I thought I was supposed to be learning about feminism, not how to memorize dates.

Professor Charania is great! Really interesting classes, and I loved the guest speakers she brought in who were all experts in their fields. She gives out a list of possible exam questions beforehand so you have lots of time to prepare and succeed in her classes. Readings are all really interesting. Looked forward to her lectures.

Very interesting prof, very controversial topics BUT if you do happen to have a different opinion on the matter of the subject you will still be respected nonetheless. She's really funny and has a very good approach for heavy subjects,doesn't make sad subjects too heavy. Very specific for what she expects from you and gave the midterm questions b4

I look forward to her lectures, and the assigned reading is interesting.  There are several controversial topics, but Prof. Charania is always positive and open to a variety of opinions.  There is a course pack rather than a textbook, and it costs roughly $19.  She is very clear in her expectations, and encourages class discussion.
Super interesting!
